JSON for representing structured data

JSON defines a data as a value
	
	json: value

where value is an elementary or structured datum

	value: nothing | logic | number | string | array | object

Elementary data:

	nothing: null (no data)
	logic: false, true
	number: 0, 1, -2, 3.45, -78.23, 12.3E3, 0.4e-4,... (*)
	string: \“clo56\”, \“X\”, \“\”,...

Structured data:

	array: [value1, value2,...] oppure [ ]
	object: {string1 : value1, string2 : value2,...} oppure { }

(*) The K language adds two number formats:
	
	#HHHHHH: 24-bit number in hexadecimal format to represent RGB color codes
	hh:mm[:ss]: 32-bit number to represent a time
